{"expireTime":9007200851391801000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-html-ast-7ad2216e727617a9a54977da8bfed915-gatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-responsive-iframegatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-smartypants-","val":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I’m incredibly excited as I write this blog and mark the start of my blogging journey.","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":87,"offset":87}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":87,"offset":87}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In the past few months, people around the world have suffered tremendous losses.","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":89},"end":{"line":4,"column":81,"offset":169}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":89},"end":{"line":4,"column":81,"offset":169}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As I write this blogpost, COVID19 is raging across the globe, numerous places in India are experiencing extreme weather conditions, Beirut has witnessed a 2700+ ton Ammonium Nitrate explosion and the Apple Fire has forced thousands to flee in California. Safe to say, 2020 has not been kind to anyone. ","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1,"offset":171},"end":{"line":6,"column":303,"offset":473}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1,"offset":171},"end":{"line":6,"column":303,"offset":473}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Oh, and here’s a great quote from this Wikipedia on\n","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":478},"end":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":530}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salted_duck_egg"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"salted duck eggs","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":2,"offset":531},"end":{"line":12,"column":18,"offset":547}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":530},"end":{"line":12,"column":66,"offset":595}}},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":66,"offset":595},"end":{"line":12,"column":67,"offset":596}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":478},"end":{"line":12,"column":67,"offset":596}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"blockquote","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A salted duck egg is a Chinese preserved food product made by soaking duck\neggs in brine, or packing each egg in damp, salted charcoal. In Asian\nsupermarkets, these eggs are sometimes sold covered in a thick layer of salted\ncharcoal paste. The eggs may also be sold with the salted paste removed,\nwrapped in plastic, and vacuum packed. From the salt curing process, the\nsalted duck eggs have a briny aroma, a gelatin-like egg white and a\nfirm-textured, round yolk that is bright orange-red in color.","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":3,"offset":600},"end":{"line":20,"column":64,"offset":1111}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":3,"offset":600},"end":{"line":20,"column":64,"offset":1111}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":598},"end":{"line":20,"column":64,"offset":1111}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"raw","value":"<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8058f3f26913fea3b6a89a73344fe94a/e1596/salty_egg.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    